# The for Loop

`for` loops are great when you know exactly how many iterations you need.

```php
for (init; condition; increment) {
    // code
}
```

1. `init` runs once at the beginning.
2. `condition` is checked before each iteration.
3. After each iteration, `increment` runs.

# More Complex for Loops

Each part can have multiple expressions separated by commas.

```php
for ($i = 0, $j = 10; $i < $j; $i++, $j--) {
    echo "i=$i, j=$j\n";
}
```

You can also omit any part, but be careful to avoid infinite loops.

```php
$i = 1;
for (; $i <= 5; ) {
    echo $i++;
}
```

